                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p><sic>page</sic> 539, I observe something like a too much waiting\n                                        upon others?<lb/> announce the meeting and I will venture to\n                                        insure an attendance of<lb/> at least a dozen—quite enough,\n                                        and perhaps better than a greater number<lb/> to resolve on\n                                        constituting itself the suggested society, which many\n                                        will<lb/> subsequently join. Forgoing that far neither much\n                                        labour nor money<lb/> will be required, whilst it may be the\n                                        means of eventual success in<lb/> the object we have in\n                                        view. If the meeting take place at <placeName>New\n                                                  York</placeName> many<lb/> of the laymen of that\n                                        city will doubtless attend. I have in view as many<lb/> as a\n                                        dozen including laymen and ministers that would be present\n                                        at the<lb/> meeting. <persName>Dr. Wise</persName><add>Each\n                                                  name is labeled with a number above it—1, 2, 3, 4,\n                                                  etc.</add>, <persName>Dr. Lilienthall</persName>,\n                                                  <persName>Revd. Mr. Isaacs</persName>,\n                                                  <persName>Revd Mr. Lyons</persName>,<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Revd Mr Leo</persName>, <persName>Revd Isaac\n                                                  Leeser</persName>, <persName>Mr Abm\n                                                  Kursheedt</persName>, His Father,<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Mr. Abm Hart</persName>\n                                        <placeName>N/Y.</placeName>\n                                        <persName>Mr. Noah</persName>, <persName>Dr. J. I.\n                                                  Cohen</persName>, <placeName>Balt.</placeName>\n                                        <persName>Revd Mr Gutheime</persName><lb/>\n                                        <persName>Revd Mr Hart</persName>,\n                                                  <placeName>Phil.</placeName> Myself. There number\n                                        14 and surely many more of<lb/> the Gentlemen from\n                                                  <placeName>Albany</placeName>, <placeName>New\n                                                  York</placeName>,\n                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, and\n                                                  <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>,<lb/> to say\n                                        nothing of <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>, &amp; other\n                                        portions of the Union who may chance<lb/> to be at\n                                                  <placeName>New York</placeName> at the time, it\n                                        may be reasonably expected will attend.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My son visited <persName>Dr. Rice</persName> at\n                                                  <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>. The\n                                        reverend<lb/> Gentleman persisted in saying he would not\n                                        attend the meeting, giving<lb/> for reason that he thought a\n                                        meeting of ministers could have no result,<lb/> and that one\n                                        of talented laymen would be likely to have more: He\n                                        added<lb/> that he might, however, yet determine on\n                                        attending. I hope he may but if<lb/> he do not we must\n                                        strive to do as well as we can without him.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Have you considered my request to have 50 copies\n                                        of each<lb/> of my letters struck off before breaking the\n                                        forms in order to their being made up<lb/> as a pamphlet. I\n                                        hope you will have the goodness to gratify me in this</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am ever revd sir Yours faithfully <persName\n                                                  role=\"author\">A A Lindo</persName></p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <div>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_6_11.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text refers to Occident Volume 6 No. 11 pages 517\n                                                  through 540. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_6_11.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text also refers to Occident Volume 6 No. 11 pages\n                                                  565 through 574. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_6_12.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text also refers to Occident Volume 6 No. 12 pages\n                                                  604 through 612. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                                        <p>\n                                                  <ref target=\"Occident_PDFs/Occ_7_1.pdf\">The above\n                                                  text also refers to Occident Volume 7 No. 1 pages\n                                                  43 through 52. Click here to view.</ref>\n                                        </p>\n                              </div>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
